name: Union Drive Marketplace
description:
The Union Drive Marketplace is located on the west side of campus in the Union Drive neighborhood. The dining center conveniently serves students living in Friley, Eaton, Martin, and Helser Halls, as well as other students and visitors to the west side of campus. The spacious, multi-venue facility offers guests more than just a meal, but a place to choose a breakfast, lunch, or dinner prepared perfectly to their liking. Country Cuisine Country Cuisine offers home-style meals. Backyard Grill Burgers, fries, specialty sandwiches, sides and more can be found at the Backyard Grill. Simple Plate Chef-created, simply balanced plates — roasted, grilled, sauteed, steamed, or baked items. There is a daily vegan option, and no gluten containing ingredients are used at Simple Plate. Most recipes in this venue do not use artificial colors/preservatives. The food is pre-portioned, so you don’t have to think about whether or not you’re serving yourself the appropriate portion size. Wok Your Way Build your own quesadilla or enjoy fresh stir-fry at Wok Your Way. Meals are prepared right in front of you on the Mongolian grill. Oregano’s Pizza, pasta, casseroles, breadsticks and more are fresh out of the oven at Oregano’s. Farmer’s Market This venue features a full salad bar, soups and also offers a salad of the day! Fresh Choice Deli Made-to-order deli sandwiches and sides can be found at the deli.
  • Deli Bundle - Available during weekday breakfast hours (6:45-10am M-F).
    After you eat breakfast, just swipe your card at the deli and get a bundle to take with you for later in the day!
    • Made-your-way deli sandwich
    • Sides (choose 3): Chips, cookie, fruit, carrots
    • Drinks (choose 1): Coke, lemonade, water
Sweet Temptations Don’t forget dessert! Sweet Temptations offers several desserts each day and there’s always soft-serve ice cream with all the toppings. Breakfast Hot home-style breakfast is served each day and the menu includes eggs, breakfast casseroles, pancakes, French toast and much more! There’s an omelet and waffle bar too. Doughnuts, pastries, bagels, fresh fruits and a cereal bar are available to get your day started right!

name: West Side Market
description: Located in the Union Drive Community Center, the West Side Market is the perfect place to run those little errands, enjoy a satisfying snack, or even grab a quick meal! The West Side Market is stocked with essentials, from batteries and pencils to soft drinks. You can also choose from a wide variety of meal and snack items, such as chips, candy, and frozen food items. Made-to-order Deli Deli sandwiches and wraps are made your way and you can even get them toasted! Try hummus or all veggies for a vegetarian option. Smack Dog A delicious Nathan's hot dog topped your way! Or, try one of our specials like the Jersey Shore or Flying Tiger. Meal Bundles Meal bundles are accepted during the following times at West Side Market: Monday-Thursday: 7:30 pm to 1 am Friday and Saturday: 7:30pm to 10pm Sunday: 4 pm to 1 am Bring Your Own Cup, Save 35 Cents! To help us all lead a more sustainable life, you can bring your own cup into any of our retail establishments and get $0.35 off of your beverage! This includes both hot beverages as well as fountain beverages.

name: South Side Market
description:
Stop by the South Side Market in the Wallace-Wilson commons to grab a meal bundle for breakfast or late-night dinner, including pizza and items from ISU Dining’s commissary kitchen. Or, get the essentials like frozen pizzas and entrees, ice-cream, snacks, candy and gum, bottled beverages, milk and dairy products, and a variety of grocery items. 

Meal Bundles are available during the following times:
Sunday: 11:00 am-midnight
Monday-Thursday:  9:00 am-1:30 pm/8:30 pm-midnight
Friday: 9 am-1:30pm/5:00pm-9:00 pm
Saturday: 11:00 am-9:00 pm

name: East Side Market
location: MWL Commons, main floor across from hall desk
description: If you're looking for a snack, quick meal, fresh pizza or just need to pick up a few essentials, stop by the East Side Market. Godfather's Pizza Express offers pizza by the slice and whole pies. You can get a sandwich at the made-to-order deli! There's snacks, beverages and frozen products. Check out the F'real machine and have a freshly blended smoothie or shake. Meal Bundles Meal bundles are accepted during the following times: Sunday - Thursday: 7:30 pm to 1 am Friday and Saturday: 7:30 pm to 10 pm Bring Your Own Cup, Save 35 Cents! To help us all lead a more sustainable life, you can bring your own cup into any of our retail establishments and get $0.35 off of your beverage! This includes both hot beverages as well as fountain beverages.

name: Business Café
description:
The Business Cafe offers a full line of The Roasterie specialty coffee drinks including lattes, mochas and more! You can also find smoothies, teas and frappes. Looking for lunch? The Business Cafe boasts a variety of fresh-packaged salads, sandwiches and wraps that are made fresh daily in our commissary kitchen. Daily soups and hot entrées are also available as well as snacks, pastries and bottled beverages. Bring Your Own Cup, Save 35 Cents!
You can bring your own cup into any of our retail establishments and get $0.35 off of your beverage (hot or fountain).

name: Clyde's FRESH EXPRESS
description:
All new for fall 2016, Clyde's Fresh Express is just that--fresh and fast! It's the perfect place to get a meal with you're on the go. Walk in, pick up what you want, swipe your card and go. Or, enjoy your meal in our dining room.

Menu items are made fresh throughout the day. Try the buffalo chicken deli sandwich, hot chicken torta sandwich, a noodle bowl, chef's salad or deep dish pizza. Make it a meal by adding fresh fried chips, a fresh veggie cup, quinoa or a homemade cookie (our campus bakery makes them fresh every day!).

Bundles are an entree, two side and fountain drink. As always, cash/credit customers are welcome.

Why is it called Clyde's? The UDCC sits on the site of the former Clyde Williams field.

name: Courtyard Café
location: W 182 Lagomarcino (Just west of the north set of Courtyard arcs)
description:
The Courtyard Café, located on the north side of campus in Lagomarcino Hall, offers a variety of soups, salads, daily hot entrées, made-to-order deli sandwiches, espresso drinks, Roasterie coffee and specialty beverages, sodas, Jet Tea smoothies, assorted pastries, and desserts. Bring Your Own Cup, Save 35 Cents!
You can bring your own cup into any of our retail establishments and get $0.35 off of your beverage (hot or fountain).

name: Design Café
location: College of Design, just off the main floor atrium
description:
Located in the College of Design on the west side of campus, the Design Café offers Roasterie coffee and specialty beverages, soups, daily hot entrées, made-to-order deli sandwiches, and a variety of fresh-packaged sandwiches and salads. Bring Your Own Cup, Save 35 Cents!
You can bring your own cup into any of our retail establishments and get $0.35 off of your beverage (hot or fountain).

name: Gentle Doctor Café
description:
The Gentle Doctor Café is located in the College of Veterinary Medicine. Try the Roasterie coffee and specialty beverages, soups and made-to-order deli sandwiches, daily hot entrées as well as fresh-packaged salads, sandwiches and wraps. For dessert, try one of our assorted pastries or an Otis Spunkmeyer cookie. Bring Your Own Cup, Save 35 Cents!
You can bring your own cup into any of our retail establishments and get $0.35 off of your beverage (hot or fountain).

name: Hawthorn
description: Hawthorn is a market, grill and cafe serving students, faculty and staff on the north side of campus. It's a great place to get a snack or meal and it's also perfect or socializing, studying and relaxing. Frederiksen Court Residents can use the gathering space even when Hawthorn is not open. Online Ordering Order online using GET Mobile! http://dining.iastate.edu/order Starbucks In addition to our full menu, Hawthorn is the only on-campus location for Starbucks coffee and specialty drinks including Frappuccinos! Convenience Products The market carries health and beauty items as well as chips, candy, groceries, bottled beverages, milk, yogurt, juices, ice cream, and frozen entrees. Bring Your Own Cup, Save 35 Cents! To help us all lead a more sustainable life, you can bring your own cup into any of our retail establishments and get $0.35 off of your beverage! This includes both hot beverages as well as fountain beverages.

name: Hub Grill & Café
description:
Centrally located, the Hub Grill & Café is a great place for meals and snacks! We offer grilled items, fresh made-to-order deli sandwiches, as well as a rotating menu of fresh-packaged salads, sandwiches and wraps. Soups, sides, desserts and fountain beverages are also available. Be sure to watch for our rotating daily special! Vending services are available 24/7. Breakfast A freshly made breakfast sandwich comes with your choice of muffin or biscuit, bacon or sausage, and it's topped with egg and cheese. You can add a combo to your breakfast that includes a fountain soda or juice and whole fruit or an AE yogurt. Breakfast is available during the academic year only (fall and spring semesters). Bring Your Own Cup, Save 35 Cents!
To help us all lead a more sustainable life, you can bring your own cup into any of our retail establishments and get $0.35 off of your beverage! This includes both hot beverages as well as fountain beverages.

name: Caribou Coffee
description: You can find Caribou Coffee's full line of beverages and tasty treats in the Hub! Fresh-brewed coffee, tea, lattes, mochas, coffee coolers, smoothies, sandwiches, salads and more make Caribou Coffee a refreshing place to relax! Sustainable Coffee It's kind of a big deal! All coffee and espresso is now 100% Rainforest Alliance Certified. Sign up at cariboucoffee.com for information about specials and coupons! Bring Your Own Cup, Save 35 Cents! To help us all lead a more sustainable life, you can bring your own cup into any of our retail establishments and get $0.35 off of your beverage! This includes both hot beverages as well as fountain beverages.

name: ABE's Harvest Café
description:
ABE's Harvest Café offers hot and cold drinks, soups, bakery items, and sandwiches, as well as hot entrées you won't want to miss! Our drinks include espresso, steamers, teas, brewed coffee, and more. Stop in at the Agricultural and Biosystems Engineering (ABE) Biorenewables Complex and make your taste buds smile. Bring Your Own Cup, Save 35 Cents!
You can bring your own cup into any of our retail establishments and get $0.35 off of your beverage.

name: Froots
description:
FROOTS offers a healthy snack or meal on the go with all-natural smoothies, shakes, fresh-squeezed juices, Yogees and more! This ISU Dining establishment also has a rotating selection of snacks, salads, wraps and sides.  

FROOTS is located in State Gym in the open-access hallway. Anyone can visit FROOTS!

Visit www.froots.com for more information about the FROOTS brand.

name: Memorial Union Food Court
description: The Memorial Union Food Court offers guests a variety of food options. The MU Food Court is also a place where students can use their meal plan to get an Express Meal! CYs & Fries Enjoy fresh (not frozen!) burgers and natural-cut fries at CYs & Fries. Fresh Burrito Works Burritos are made your way! Chester's Chicken Chicken sandwiches, chicken strips, french fries and more can be found at Chester's Chicken. Cucina Italiana Chicken parmesan, spaghetti, and all your favorite Italian dishes are available at Cucina Italiana. The Dish The Dish boasts a menu of international dishes, home-cooked comfort foods, soups and sides. The Dish also offers hot breakfast items. Godfather's Pizza An offer that's too good to be true! Godfather's pizza is available in the MU Food Court, including during breakfast! Deli case and desserts are also available in the MU Food Court.

name: Bookends Café
location: Parks Library, Room 0184, adjacent to the Fire Place Room
description:
Bookends Café offers a full line of Roasterie coffees and specialty beverages, Jet Tea smoothies, frappes and hot chocolate. Pair your beverage with a fresh-baked pastry. Looking for lunch? Bookends Café boasts a variety of fresh-packaged salads, sandwiches and wraps that are made fresh daily in our commissary kitchen. Bring Your Own Cup, Save 35 Cents!
You can bring your own cup into any of our retail establishments and get $0.35 off of your beverage (hot or fountain).

name: MU Market & Café
location: Memorial Union, Ground Floor; near the Iowa State University Book Store's north entrance
description:
Enjoy the convenience of a cafe, smoothie bar and c-store in one location! We have Roasterie Coffee and specialty beverages, Freshens smoothies, fresh-packaged salads, wraps, sandwiches and sides. You'll also find pastries and desserts along with a wide variety of convenience items including Amy's organic/vegetarian meals. Bring Your Own Cup, Save 35 Cents!
You can bring your own cup into any of our retail establishments and get $0.35 off of your beverage (hot or fountain).

name: Seasons Marketplace
description: This state-of-the-art dining center features six specialty stations, meeting space and more! Bonsai's Bonsai's is an international specialty station and features stir-fry and grilled items. Bushel Basket Create your own salad or enjoy the salad of the day! There's also fresh fruits and a full salad bar. Visit the Bushel Basket's deli for a delicious sandwich. Cocoa Bean Cozy up in the Cocoa Bean for breakfast or dessert. This venue looks like mom's kitchen (only bigger!) and serves cereal, breads, pastries, desserts, coffee, bakery items, ice cream and more! Hickory's Enjoy smoked meats from Hickory's smoker! Top your entree with our signature barbeque sauce developed by an ISU Dining chef. You'll find home-cooked foods, sides and smoked meats at Hickory's. Olive Branch This full-service Italian venue boasts freshly prepared gourmet pizzas, calzones, breadsticks and casseroles all baked in a stone hearth oven. Wood Grill Traditional made-to-order grilled sandwiches and sides can be found at the Wood Grill. Breakfast Hot home-style breakfast is served each day and the menu includes eggs, breakfast casseroles, pancakes, French toast and much more. Doughnuts, pastries, bagels, fresh fruits and a cereal bar are available to get your day started right!

name: Storms Dining
description:
Located on the south side of campus, Storms Dining offers all-you-care-to-eat dinner service Sunday through Thursdays evenings. Primarily serving residents of Wallace and Wilson halls, Storms Dining features pizzas, salad and deli stations, fresh made-to-order American fare creations, fresh-made bakery items, Blue Bunny ice cream and a create your own concept. Storms also features plenty of vegetarian and some gluten-free items as well as a number of local, sustainable and healthy items.

Storms has been redesigned for the 2012-13 school year and features new furniture and a vibrant atmosphere. It’s also a great place to grab a meal on the go with ISU Dining’s To-Go Program!

name: Global Café
description:
The Global Cafe is located in the Harl Commons of Curtiss Hall. You can find Burgie's brewed coffee, hot tea, freshly baked pastries and desserts, snacks, soup, sandwiches, salads, wraps and bottled beverages. Coffee that Makes a Difference
Global Cafe offers a high-quality, fair-trade coffee that is grown by farmers in Uganda. The College of Agriculture and Life Sciences will donate proceeds to the Center for Sustainable Rural Livelihoods, a college program helping farmers and families in rural Uganda. Drink a cup and make a global difference. Bring Your Own Cup, Save 35 Cents!
You can bring your own cup into any of our retail establishments and get $0.35 off of your beverage (hot or fountain).

name: Friley Windows
description:
Welcome to our newest dining center! With an industrial feel, Friley Windows is designed to be a place you can have dinner with your entire house or just swing in, grab a snack and study solo. 

Three large serving stations offer classic favorites, international cuisine, fresh pizza, desserts a salad bar and a vegan station.
